item.title: Where is EGUI.JAVA?
item.dc:creator: @ouassim ouassim
item.description:
@ouassim wrote:

i think its not closed. because it has a tut for changing ur server ip
only i can not find it pls help me:

[1] Go to my Client folder. Then scroll down until you see a folder called “EGUI.JAVA”

[2]Open it up. And look towards the bottom.

[3] You should see 3 things in a line that say. “0.0.0.0”

[4] Go up to “Edit” and then “Replace…”

[5] The box should look like this…

┌––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––┐
| Replace |
|__________________________________________|
| |
| Find What: 0.0.0.0 Find Next |
| Replace |
| Replace All |
| Cancel |
| Replace with: YourIP |
| |
| |
| |
| Match Case |
| |
└––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––┘

[6] Thats what it should look like. Where it says “YourIP”. Thats your clients ip address. Not your computers IP address
